# Cloudflare R2 Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

R2_ACCOUNT_ID=your-account-id-here
R2_ACCESS_KEY=your-access-key-here
R2_SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here
R2_BUCKET_NAME=your-bucket-name-here

# How to get these values:
# 1. Go to Cloudflare Dashboard → R2 Object Storage
# 2. Create a bucket or use existing one (R2_BUCKET_NAME)
# 3. Go to Manage R2 API tokens → Create API token
# 4. Copy Account ID (R2_ACCOUNT_ID)
# 5. Copy Access Key ID (R2_ACCESS_KEY) and Secret Access Key (R2_SECRET_KEY)
